1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,294
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,378 --> 00:00:05,380
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,468
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:12,762
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,561
[Ibyang] <i>Master Grumpy</i>
<i>is looking for my parents?</i>

7
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:21,020
[elated shriek]

8
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:23,815
[Ibyang] <i>I'm sure</i>
<i>Master Grumpy will find them!</i>

9
00:00:23,898 --> 00:00:25,191
[Sister Ludy] <i>Sister Norma!</i>

10
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:26,192
- Run!
- [Red] Her?

11
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:27,110
[grunting]

12
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:28,194
[gunshots blasting]

13
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,904
[grunts]

14
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,114
[Atoy] Sister, you should escape now!

15
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:34,367
[Atoy] <i>If you want Sister Norma,</i>
<i>you'll have to go through me first.</i>

16
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:35,577
[Red, in English] <i>So be it.</i>

17
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,162
[grunting]

18
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:39,873
[Red] <i>Your voice sounds familiar.</i>

19
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:41,124
<i>Have I met you before?</i>

20
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:42,584
<i>Show your ugly face.</i>

21
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:45,086
[Atoy] I bet you are way uglier than me.

22
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:47,422
PREVIOUSLY

23
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:48,757
[Red] <i>Face him.</i>

24
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:50,341
<i>Sister Norma is mine.</i>

25
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:55,055
<i>Tell me where you took</i>
<i>the child Martina left with you.</i>

26
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:58,349
I will not tell you
where she is, you devil!

27
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,642
You'll only hurt her!

28
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:00,643
[Atoy] <i>Sister Norma!</i>

29
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:02,729
- [bell tolls]
- [groans]

30
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:04,439
[Red] Where's the child?
Where's the child?

31
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:07,317
[screams]

32
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,526
- [thuds]
- [gasps]

33
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,904
[nun 1] <i>Why did you have to kill her?</i>

34
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:12,989
[Atoy] <i>I hope you can</i>
<i>forgive me, Sister Norma.</i>

35
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,783
- <i>I failed to protect you.</i>
- [sirens blaring]

36
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:25,168
[sneaky music playing]

37
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:35,720
Ibyang, maybe you should go to sleep now.

38
00:01:35,804 --> 00:01:37,764
We'll update you tomorrow.

39
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,599
You're so sleepy already.

40
00:01:39,682 --> 00:01:43,728
Oh, um, Ms. Cita, I'm not sleepy.

41
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:47,106
Look. Look at my eyes.

42
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:49,859
I'm wide awake.

43
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:56,241
- Mmm, oh?
- [Ibyang] Oh.

44
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:58,201
[mellow music playing]

45
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,995
- [sighs]
- [Ibyang panting]

46
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:07,585
Ibyang is just excited
to know her real parents.

47
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:12,006
What about you, Ame? Are you excited?

48
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:14,884
I'm excited.

49
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:17,387
I just don't want to see
Ibyang disappointed.

50
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:20,849
[Tonet] Why? Do you think Atoy
won't find them?

51
00:02:21,891 --> 00:02:23,226
[Karla] Exactly, Ame.

52
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:25,103
Brother Atoy was able to save you.

53
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:26,354
He can definitely do that too.

54
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:29,691
- [Cita] Poor child.
- [Karla] Ibyang.

55
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,820
Hey, Brother Atoy!

56
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:35,822
Did you find Ibyang's parents?

57
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,702
[somber music playing]

58
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:42,162
Um…

59
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:45,331
[in English] Sorry, Ibyang.

60
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,584
[melancholic music playing]

61
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,210
[Atoy] I was wrong.

62
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:52,213
The one who knew
your parents wasn't there.

63
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:55,633
Don't worry, Ibyang.

64
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:58,845
Atoy will do everything
to find your parents.

65
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:02,515
Yes! Just trust him!

66
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,726
Brother Atoy's mission is just beginning.

67
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:06,060
Right, bro?

68
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,147
[Atoy] Huh? Yes, of course.

69
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:11,649
[Tonet] Okay, that's enough.

70
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:13,693
Come on. Let's go to bed.

71
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:17,155
- Come on, come on.
- We'll sleep now.

72
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:18,948
[Tonet] It's fine.

73
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:30,793
[suave theme music playing]

74
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:34,964
[motorcycle revving]

75
00:03:57,779 --> 00:04:03,076
The only person who knew
how we could find Audrey's child is dead.

76
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:05,245
[in English] Under your watch.

77
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:08,373
Weren't you listening to my story?

78
00:04:08,456 --> 00:04:10,041
Someone interfered, okay?!

79
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,584
Pretended to be a nun!

80
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,419
[pensive music playing]

81
00:04:13,503 --> 00:04:16,047
I'll find that bastard.
I can't let this go.

82
00:04:16,547 --> 00:04:17,966
[in English] Are… Are you serious
right now, hon?

83
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,759
[in English] Are you… Are you
even listening to yourself?

84
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:22,345
He went against me!

85
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:23,972
I can't let that go.

86
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:26,224
My plan was ruined because of him.

87
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,351
[in English] You and your ego!

88
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:31,938
Do you think that will help us
find Audrey's child?

89
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:34,148
[Martina sighs]

90
00:04:35,024 --> 00:04:36,359
Did this person see you?

91
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,153
No.

92
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,155
[in English] Well, then he's the least
of our problems.

93
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:46,327
Right now, we need to find other ways
to get your sister's child back.

94
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,204
How? Sister Norma is dead.

95
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,122
[scoffs]

96
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:51,833
[Martina, softly, in English] My God.

97
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:54,877
[sinister music playing]

98
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:56,045
[door clicks shut]

99
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:06,389
[tense music playing]

100
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:07,765
[Atoy] Sister, you should escape now!

101
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:10,601
- [shrieks]
- [Atoy] Sister Norma!

102
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:11,894
[sinister music playing]

103
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,814
Find her.

104
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:37,420
Atoy…

105
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:39,047
[pensive music playing]

106
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:41,424
What really happened?

107
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:47,764
I made a mistake, Godmother.

108
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:50,975
I know you.

109
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:54,312
You don't make mistakes
when it comes to your work.

110
00:05:56,272 --> 00:06:00,068
Atoy, weren't you able
to talk to Sister Norma?

111
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,903
Wasn't she at the convent?

112
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,201
We were supposed to meet.

113
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:12,246
She was going to tell me
who gave Ibyang up for adoption.

114
00:06:17,376 --> 00:06:19,212
But then two men came.

115
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,755
[tense sting]

116
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,924
Two masked men…

117
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,345
I don't know what they wanted from her.

118
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:34,602
Because of them, Sister Norma is gone.

119
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:37,814
- [Cita] What?
- Sister Norma is gone?

120
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:39,941
[pensive music playing]

121
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:45,530
She handed me this before she died.

122
00:06:45,613 --> 00:06:46,656
What's this?

123
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,950
[Ame] Martin?

124
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,952
Does that mean he's Ibyang's father?

125
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,205
[sighs]

126
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,623
[tense music playing]

127
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,250
I don't know.

128
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:00,461
I don't know if it's
a first name or a surname.

129
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,171
I don't know.

130
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:07,718
[inhales] But I know Sister Norma
wanted to tell me more.

131
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,304
But she's gone.

132
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,931
And I'll never know.

133
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:16,727
[Atoy sighs]

134
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:28,281
It's normal to feel sad, Ibyang.

135
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,953
I'm not sad.

136
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:39,876
I didn't have parents even before.

137
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:43,421
Nothing new about that.

138
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:45,298
[melancholic music playing]

139
00:07:45,381 --> 00:07:47,967
Brother Atoy will never give up.

140
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,802
He'll continue searching.

141
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:51,471
You'll see!

142
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:58,269
I'm okay, Sis Karla.

143
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,689
It's fine. I'm okay.

144
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:03,900
I'll go to sleep now.

145
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:07,695
I still have school early tomorrow.

146
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:08,863
It's fine.

147
00:08:10,448 --> 00:08:12,992
Good night. I'll have my beauty rest.

148
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:16,704
[in English] Okay. Good night, Ibyang!

149
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:19,707
- [smooches] Say your prayers.
- Good night.

150
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,834
[in English] Good night, baby.

151
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:22,877
Let's go, Karla.

152
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,219
[melancholic music playing]

153
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:54,659
[sobbing]

154
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:24,814
Ibyang's request for porridge
as her packed meal is unusual, huh?

155
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:26,482
Porridge?

156
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:28,442
Why not? It's delicious!

157
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:30,444
In Cebu, we always eat that.

158
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:33,406
[muffled chattering in the distance]

159
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:34,365
[Paldo, in English] Oh my God!

160
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:37,410
- Baby Tonet!
- Oh!

161
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:40,288
- He said "Baby Tonet".
- [Paldo, in English] Good morning!

162
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,164
[men, in English] Good morning!

163
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,166
- [man 1] Yiee-hiee!
- It's a beautiful morning, isn't it?

164
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:48,087
But it's nothing compared to your beauty.

165
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,839
[men teasing]

166
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:51,674
- [Karla] There you go!
- [man] That was beautiful.

167
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,384
The day just got ugly.

168
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,303
- [whimsical flourish]
- [sneaky music playing]

169
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,929
[in English] Ah, good morning, Paldo.

170
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,931
- [in English] Good morning.
- [men, in English] Morning!

171
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:02,143
Um, do you have plans later?

172
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,020
Maybe we can go on a date?

173
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,355
You know, there's
a good place to eat here.

174
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:09,650
I wanted to invite you.
You don't have plans later!

175
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:11,110
- [men] Yes!
- [Paldo] So, we'll eat out.

176
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:12,153
- [man 1] Yiee.
- Right? Right?

177
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:13,613
- [man 1] Of course!
- [man 2] Yes!

178
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,741
Why does it feel like
you're answering for me?

179
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:20,036
No, it's just positive thinking.

180
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,830
- [man 2] Mmm-hmm.
- Where do you get that, Paldo?

181
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,665
Get what?

182
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:26,834
That misplaced sense of confidence.

183
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:29,128
- Hmm, that's really misplaced.
- Yes.

184
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:30,671
- Misplaced indeed.
- That's how Cap is.

185
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:32,923
- Mmm-mmm.
- A lot. A whole lot.

186
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:35,468
You've been at it for a while now.

187
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:36,552
Don't be annoying.

188
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,889
- Okay.
- So, Baby Tonet…

189
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,559
What? Are you going out with me?

190
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:46,562
[in English] You know,
is it a yes or a yes?

191
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,731
[men, in English] Yes! Yes! Yes!

192
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:51,233
- [man 3] Yes, of course!
- [Paldo] Yes? Yes?

193
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:53,361
Nope. No.

194
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,987
- No, sorry.
- [Paldo] Uh…

195
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:57,031
- That's my answer.
- No?

196
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:00,284
All right, maybe next time.

197
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:01,202
There are plenty of days.

198
00:11:01,285 --> 00:11:03,496
[in English] I'll make time for you, okay?

199
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,122
[in English] Just… Just tell me.

200
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,332
[in English] I'll make time for you.

201
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:09,043
- [in English] Don't worry, baby.
- [man 3] Anytime, he's available.

202
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:12,630
Didn't you understand what I said?

203
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:15,883
It's really not possible,
because someone already owns my heart.

204
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,636
There's… There's a TTH who owns it.

205
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:21,013
- Oh.
- Wait. What… What's TTH?

206
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:22,181
What… What's TTH?

207
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,518
Never mind. You don't know that,
and you're not like that.

208
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:28,396
So, does that mean Cap got rejected?

209
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:29,647
Ah, you nailed it!

210
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:31,899
[laughs, in English] Very good! Yes!

211
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:34,068
Sorry, no.

212
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:38,531
So, you weren't able
to talk to Ms. Norma Cruz?

213
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:40,366
Yes, that's why we're here again.

214
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:41,367
Just a favor.

215
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,618
[in English] Can you just please
give us the names

216
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:45,663
of all the 8-year-olds
that were adopted that year?

217
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:47,164
I'm sorry, ma'am.

218
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:49,375
Those records are confidential.

219
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,669
It's the institution's policy.

220
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:53,129
[pensive music playing]

221
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:58,509
[Martina, in English]
How sure are you about that policy?

222
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:01,303
[tense music playing]

223
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:14,567
[in English] Oh my!

224
00:12:15,234 --> 00:12:16,277
You know…

225
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:18,696
Are you sure about that?

226
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:20,865
- [man 1] Damn!
- Are you sure?

227
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:23,617
- Look at it.
- [man 1] Oh, oh.

228
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:25,536
Are you going to waste my good looks?

229
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,246
- [man 3] Oh!
- [man 2] Will you waste that?!

230
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:30,249
My masculinity, huh?

231
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,001
- [man 1] Hmm, feel it!
- [man 3] He's a tough guy!

232
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:33,043
[Paldo] You don't want this?

233
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:38,257
You know… you'll regret this.

234
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:42,428
When I get rich, you'll be a nobody to me.

235
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:44,096
- [man 1] He's gonna be rich.
- [Paldo] So, if I were you,

236
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,639
think about it.

237
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:46,974
But don't worry.

238
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:49,810
[in English] I'll give you another chance.

239
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:51,103
[man 1, in English] Another chance.

240
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,480
[sneaky music playing]

241
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:55,649
[man 3] Aw. Cap is really sweet!

242
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:57,193
- Girl, wash your hands.
- [Paldo, in English] Let's go, let's go.

243
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:58,235
[Paldo, in English] Take your time.

244
00:12:58,319 --> 00:13:00,070
[indistinct chattering]

245
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,990
- [phone rings]
- [retches]

246
00:13:05,075 --> 00:13:07,286
[clears throat]

247
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:11,207
Hello, Gavin?

248
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:13,167
What? What's the news?

249
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:17,087
[Gavin] <i>Karla, I really thought</i>
<i>about what you told me last time.</i>

250
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,381
[in English] <i>About wasting time</i>
<i>when it comes to love.</i>

251
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:21,884
[Karla] Oh, really?

252
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:24,887
I thought about it too.

253
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,515
[Gavin] <i>Can we meet?</i>

254
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:29,850
<i>I just have something important</i>
<i>to tell you.</i>

255
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:32,811
[light feel-good music playing]

256
00:13:35,689 --> 00:13:38,984
Um… Okay!

257
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:44,448
Martina, Martina, wait.

258
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:46,450
- [in English] What?
- Oh?

259
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:49,537
Now that you've gathered
all the names of 8-year-old girls,

260
00:13:50,454 --> 00:13:52,748
how will we find Audrey's real daughter?

261
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:54,917
[in English] It doesn't matter.

262
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,044
We'll look for a girl the same age
as Audrey's daughter,

263
00:13:57,127 --> 00:14:00,714
and then, we'll convince
the parents to hand over their child.

264
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,383
Are you serious?

265
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:03,759
‪[sinister music playing]

266
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:05,636
Do you think the parents
will just give her up?

267
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:08,264
What? Are you going
to cover it up with money again?

268
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:11,141
[scoffs, in English] Name me one thing
that money can't buy, hon.

269
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,601
What if the adoptive family is rich?

270
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:15,646
Then we'll choose a family
who can be easily blinded by money.

271
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:18,899
[rousing music playing]

272
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:24,947
[Atoy] Oh, how are you?

273
00:14:26,323 --> 00:14:27,366
You okay now?

274
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,660
Are you ready to go to school?

275
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,246
Hmm, I'm okay.

276
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:34,540
Why, Master?

277
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:38,043
Eh…

278
00:14:39,753 --> 00:14:41,463
Of course, because…

279
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:46,594
I failed in my mission.
I didn't find your…

280
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:47,553
Oh, no!

281
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:50,890
The porridge is dripping.

282
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:52,933
Won't I spill it?

283
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,436
What? Porridge?

284
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:57,855
[pleasant music playing]

285
00:14:57,938 --> 00:14:59,189
There's nothing…

286
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:00,774
Why did you even choose this?

287
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:05,487
What normal student would want
to bring porridge to school?

288
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:08,741
Who said I'm normal?

289
00:15:08,824 --> 00:15:11,160
I'm special!

290
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:13,787
There we go.

291
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:14,872
Oh.

292
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:18,083
Hey.

293
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:19,668
What's this again?

294
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,670
Where are you sneaking off to?

295
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,465
You've got yellow paint.

296
00:15:24,548 --> 00:15:26,091
Seems like it.

297
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,802
Aren't you leaving?

298
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,681
Why? Are you telling me to leave?

299
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:36,393
- No, I'm just asking.
- Mmm.

300
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:39,730
I just need to buy something at the store.

301
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:41,398
- Ibyang, what are you--
- [phone ringing]

302
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:42,650
What are you going to buy?

303
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,194
Wait. Sir?

304
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:47,404
Oh, okay, huh?

305
00:15:47,488 --> 00:15:48,614
Psst, hey.

306
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:50,532
- [Ibyang] I just need to buy something!
- Okay.

307
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:52,201
Yes, sir?

308
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:55,329
[mysterious music playing]

309
00:16:07,007 --> 00:16:09,593
Uh, brother…

310
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:15,432
- [man] What is it?
- Do you have… super glue?

311
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:16,934
Uh, wait a moment.

312
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:18,185
I'll check at the back.

313
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,105
‪Ah…

314
00:16:25,192 --> 00:16:28,696
[whimsical music playing]

315
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:37,663
Here.

316
00:16:38,914 --> 00:16:39,832
Yes, sir?

317
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,876
I'll check now. Wait.

318
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:51,927
Okay. [sighs]

319
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:56,098
Here.

320
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:07,067
I found it.

321
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,235
I got the file.

322
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:12,406
All right.

323
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:27,546
[distant chattering]

324
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,564
‪[melancholic music playing]

325
00:17:57,076 --> 00:18:00,788
[bright music playing]

326
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:01,997
Ibyang!

327
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:04,416
Hi!

328
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,794
- [Ibyang] Miss Audrey!
- [Audrey laughs]

329
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,088
Come, let's go here.

330
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:12,800
How are you?

331
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:15,427
Ah, I'll use this.

332
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:16,386
All right.

333
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,097
Ah, thank you.

334
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:23,644
[vendor] Where's that girl?

335
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:25,479
- Boss.
- Boss?

336
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:26,688
[quirky music playing]

337
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:28,440
Did a child come in here?

338
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,733
Uh, a student.

339
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:32,277
[vendor] Many children come in here, boss.

340
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,364
Uh, this student
is about this… this height?

341
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,325
[vendor] Well, many children
come in here, boss.

342
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,037
Son of a thread.

343
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:45,582
[sneaky music playing]

344
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,966
[Atoy] Where are you
sneaking off to again?

345
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:56,093
You've got yellow paint.

346
00:18:59,346 --> 00:19:03,809
I brought my exchange food! Here it is!

347
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:08,188
[chuckles softly]

348
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,858
[in English] Soft food.

349
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:12,860
[in English] Oh, wow!

350
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:15,404
Aww, you're so sweet.

351
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:19,116
Sorry, I didn't bring anything.

352
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:21,660
[Audrey exclaims]

353
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:23,704
- [in English] Cookies!
- This is delicious!

354
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:25,414
- Wow!
- Still fresh!

355
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:28,709
[in English] Oatmeal, chocolate oatmeal.

356
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:31,044
There's even chocolate!

357
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,754
[both gasp]

358
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:33,797
Let me taste it.

359
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,507
Go ahead, taste it.

360
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:38,635
- [light music playing]
- Mmm…

361
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:42,097
- Is it good?
- Mmm…

362
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,182
Is it okay?

363
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:44,808
- It's delicious!
- Oh!

364
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:46,393
This is my favorite now.

365
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:49,021
- I'll eat too.
- Wait, just a moment.

366
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:50,814
I'll get the spoon.

367
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:53,734
[gentle music playing]

368
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:55,736
Here.

369
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,363
[in English] Thank you.

370
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:04,369
Mmm.

371
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:11,001
Oh, sorry. That's probably lukewarm now.

372
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:15,756
You've already done so much for me.

373
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:20,427
You even brought me soft food. [chuckles]

374
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:23,722
I just asked my sisters to buy it.

375
00:20:24,389 --> 00:20:26,892
You! You even baked for me!

376
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:29,853
- Isn't that harder?
- [chuckles]

377
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:35,150
[chuckling, sobbing]

378
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:41,365
Does it taste that bad?

379
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:43,700
[sobs, chuckles]

380
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:48,205
[muffled chattering in the distance]

381
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:50,666
- Bro?
- [Atoy] Bro.

382
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,251
- [painter] Yes, sir?
- Uh…

383
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:55,379
Which one here has…

384
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:59,132
yellow paint?

385
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,219
Maybe new paint?

386
00:21:02,302 --> 00:21:05,973
Uh, I painted some benches at the park.

387
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,474
- At the park?
- Yes.

388
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:09,351
- You did it yourself?
- Yes.

389
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:11,019
[suspicious music playing]

390
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:11,937
- All right.
- Oh.

391
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:13,730
- Bro, where's the park?
- Over here.

392
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:19,361
Ah, don't cry anymore.

393
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:20,904
Don't cry anymore.

394
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:27,577
Next time, I'll buy you
a yummier porridge, and hot too.

395
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:32,791
[muffled chattering in the distance]

396
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:36,586
This porridge is perfect, Ibyang.

397
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:41,758
[inhales] I was just
wishfully thinking that…

398
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:44,636
[sobs] I hope…

399
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:48,432
I hope my child is as kind as you.

400
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:49,933
Huh?

401
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:52,227
Why?

402
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,729
Is she naughty?

403
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:54,855
[sniffles]

404
00:21:56,606 --> 00:22:00,444
I'm just sad because
I'm not with her right now.

405
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,365
[sobbing]

406
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:10,037
It seems both our lives are full of drama.

407
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:13,415
Huh?

408
00:22:13,498 --> 00:22:15,834
Uh, what-what do you mean?

409
00:22:16,543 --> 00:22:18,795
Aren't you with your mother now?

410
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:21,798
Kind of.

411
00:22:23,425 --> 00:22:25,218
[sniffles, in English] I'm so sorry.

412
00:22:26,553 --> 00:22:27,637
[in English] I'm so sorry.

413
00:22:28,388 --> 00:22:29,598
Well, you know…

414
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:33,018
despite what happened to us,

415
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:36,730
at least, we still have each other.

416
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:39,608
- Right?
- Yes.

417
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:42,694
[sighs]

418
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:45,322
[optimistic music playing]

419
00:22:58,627 --> 00:23:02,089
[light music playing]

420
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:04,716
This child already knows
how to skip class.

421
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:25,445
- [electronic blipping]
- [tense music playing]

422
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:34,037
Does your adopted child
give you a headache?

423
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:35,497
She causes me pain all over!

424
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:38,208
I'm willing to pay a lot of money.

425
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:39,626
Just give me the child.

426
00:23:39,709 --> 00:23:40,627
[Janine] Hey, Ibyang!

427
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:44,172
You even brought your neighbor
to pretend to be your father, huh.

428
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:45,674
What are you saying?

429
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:47,634
I'm her father.

430
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:49,594
[Roma] <i>I found your real mother.</i>

431
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:50,762
UP NEXT

432
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:52,472
[in English] This mission is delicate.

433
00:23:52,556 --> 00:23:54,516
[Mercado] <i>Because it involves a child.</i>

434
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:56,268
<i>We can't be reckless.</i>

435
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:58,019
[Atoy] <i>I'll take care of this.</i>

436
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:00,230
<i>I'll find out when the father leaves,</i>

437
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:02,190
<i>so I can find a window.</i>

438
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:05,694
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

439
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,738
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

440
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:11,658
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
